# Coding standards

The canonical coding standards live in `AGENTS.md` at the repository root.

## Rules

- Follow `AGENTS.md § Coding style and naming` for TypeScript, Python, formatting, and naming.
- Follow `AGENTS.md § Build, test, and development commands` for package-manager and command choices.
- Use `npm` for this monorepo and `uv` for `Projects/GRID-main` Python work.
- Keep server-specific logic inside its workspace; share common code via `Components/*`.
- If this file conflicts with `AGENTS.md`, `AGENTS.md` wins.
